transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Vagra.

Speaker 2: Hi, yes.

Speaker 1: My name is Gerardo Jameos and I am calling to cancel my prescription with you guys.

Speaker 2: Let me pull your prescription for you, okay.

Speaker 1: May I have the phone number you used for the prescription, sir?

Speaker 2: It's 303-619-9824.

Speaker 1: Mr. Gerardo Jaramillo?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, you have a prescription for Viagra 50 mg from Dr. Noyes, 10 tablets every 30 days.

Speaker 2: You just don't need those refilled at the moment or any health concern?

Speaker 1: No, you know, I've been doing it for the last three months and I have a lot of those,

Speaker 2: so I don't need any of those right now.

Speaker 1: Yes, you can pause.

Speaker 2: I can tell the pharmacy to pause.

Speaker 1: They're going to stop the original writing from the doctor, which is every 30 days,

Speaker 2: and they pause the prescription so you can order as needed.

Speaker 1: So what that allows you is that you can order at the same price.

Speaker 2: You don't pay more expensive price when you need it in the future.

Speaker 1: But you're just not going to get it every month because you have a lot left,

Speaker 2: so you need to finish what you have first, basically.

Speaker 1: They'll pause you, I think, every half a year, and then you can get it once or twice a year,

Speaker 2: but not necessarily every month.

Speaker 1: If you don't need it, there is no reason for you to receive it every month.

Speaker 2: You know what I mean?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Yes, so I can advise the pharmacy to pause.

Speaker 1: So they're going to stop the original 30 days from the doctor, and you're going to order as needed.

Speaker 2: They're going to pause up to half a year, and you can call to reorder when you're done, okay?

Speaker 1: You're going to have a quick refill button activity in the account on your dashboard,

Speaker 2: and you can press that and get your refill, or you give us a call, you know?

Speaker 1: Yes, I can probably give you guys a call and refill.

Speaker 2: Okay, so let me pause you for now, and then you can call to reorder, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, that sounds good.

Speaker 2: All right, so you're all set, Mr. Jaramillo.

Speaker 1: Thank you for making time to call.

Speaker 2: I advise the pharmacy to put a pause for half a year and call us to reorder

Speaker 1: or log into your account, press your quick refill button.

Speaker 2: Okay, that sounds good.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
